<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="conscious-adj">conscious <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'kɒnʃəs/    美 /'kɑːnʃəs/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-aware">1.★ <strong>察觉到的；意识到的(aware)：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>(be) conscious of:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The greatest of faults is to be conscious of none.
最大的错误是没有意识到错误。</p><footer>——托马斯·卡莱尔</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) conscious + that 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>To be conscious that you are ignorant is a great step to knowledge. 
意识到自己无知等于向知识迈出了一大步。</p><footer>——狄斯雷利</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>有知觉的；神志清醒的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 unconscious </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>After he became conscious, he remembered having been attacked and hit on the head.
醒过来后，他记起自己被人袭击了头部。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>有意识的；关注的；注重的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Not all body language is conscious.
不是所有的肢体语言都是有意识的。</p><footer>外研④ – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>environmentally conscious consumers 
有环保意识的消费者</p></div></div>